    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the decorative and architectural style in 19th century America associated with the furniture designs of Charles Locke Eastlake. In architecture, the style derives forms from furniture design featuring columns resembling table legs, curved brackets, spindles, and knobs of various shapes consisting of circular perforations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo decorativo y arquitectónico del siglo XIX en América asociado con los diseños de muebles de Charles Locke Eastlake. En arquitectura, el estilo obtiene formas de los diseños de muebles y presenta columnas que se parecen a las patas de la mesa, soportes curvados, husos, y perillas de varias formas consistentes en perforaciones circulares.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de decoratieve en architecturale stijl in 19de-eeuws Amerika die is verbonden met de meubelontwerpen van Charles Locke Eastlake. In architectuur ontleent deze stijl vormen aan meubelontwerpen, met zuilen die op tafelpoten lijken, gekromde draagstenen, spijlen en knoppen met verschillende vormen die bestaan uit cirkelvormige perforaties.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指美國十九世紀時，與查理斯‧洛克‧伊斯特列克（Charles Locke Eastlake）的家具設計有關之裝飾及建築風格。建築方面，該風格是由家具設計衍生而來，以類似桌腳的圓柱、弧形托架、紡錘形柱，及由圓形穿孔器所構成之各式各樣的門把手為特色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
